Commentary Text: Harshal Patel to Rahul Chahar, out Lbw!! There's the hat-trick. Rahul Chahar doesn't even bother to review. Walks back. Beautiful off-cutter which dips as a full-toss at the last moment, Chahar didn't pick it at all and saw the ball strike the pad right in front before he could get the bat in the ball's way. Remember Chris Cairns to Chris Read in a Test match where the batter ducked and saw the loopy full-toss hit the stumps. Look that one up on YouTube. HawkEye shows it to be clipping the base of leg-stump. Kohli and the RCB team are pumped. No-one can stop them from celebrating. Rahul Chahar lbw b Harshal Patel 0(1)

Commentary Text: Harshal Patel to Pollard, out Bowled!! That should be the game. Two in two for Harshal Patel. Pollard has made a mental error there, shuffles across too much, exposes his middle and leg-stump, the off-cutter sneaks past the flick and hits the stumps. Harshal Patel is jumping around for joy. Can't understand what Pollard was thinking there, looking for a nudge to leg instead of trusting his power-hitting. Kohli doesn't care though - he plants a kiss on Harshal's head. Now Harshal on a hat-trick. Pollard b Harshal Patel 7(10)
